The paper discusses a gathering algorithm for agents that act in the plane and are identical and indistinguishable, which suggests that it belongs to the Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) sub-category. The agents have simple sensors and can only detect the presence of other agents in front or behind them, which implies that it could also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The paper presents a probabilistic algorithm, which could also place it in the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The agents lack any means of direct communication and do not have a common frame of reference, which suggests that it could belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of random orientations and continuous sensing and motion, which could also place it in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
